title: Learn European Portuguese with Portuguese With Leo [EN, PT subtitles]
description:
Aprende Português Europeu através de conteúdos interessantes e autênticos!

Neste episódio introdutório vamos falar sobre O QUE É o Portuguese With Leo e COMO o podem usar para melhorar o vosso português.

Vamos falar sobre 2 métodos diferentes de aprender línguas: o Método Tradicional, que é o que está presente na maioria das escolas de línguas, e o Método Natural, que foi desenvolvido pelo liguista Stephen Krashen e tenta seguir a forma natural como aprendemos as nossas línguas nativas.

Ver os meus vídeos vai ajudar a expor-vos à língua portuguesa, o que irá gradualmente ajudar-vos a melhorar o vosso português enquanto aprendem mais sobre temas interessantes e atuais. 
--------------------------------------------------------------------

ACEDE A CONTEÚDOS EXCLUSIVOS NO PATREON:
https://www.patreon.com/portuguesewithleo

APOIA O CANAL COM UMA PEQUENA DOAÇÃO:
https://www.portuguesewithleo.com/donate

OUVE O PODCAST:
Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/show/0tex61CKrQ0InxdgdRmqf7?si=HX8K5bntQr-MRaPACK3AjQ
iTunes: https://podcasts.apple.com/pt/podcast/portuguese-with-leo/id1523344579
Google Podcasts: https://podcasts.google.com/feed/aHR0cHM6Ly9mZWVkcy5yZWRjaXJjbGUuY29tLzI0MjBkNTNhLTg3YWEtNDEwMS04ZWI4LTVkNDIyNWQ3MjkyMw==

WEBSITE:
https://www.portuguesewithleo.com/

REDES SOCIAIS:
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/portuguesewithleo/
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/portuguesewithleo/

EMAIL:
leo@portuguesewithleo.com

Música:
Slowly by Smith The Mister https://smiththemister.bandcamp.com 
Smith The Mister https://bit.ly/Smith-The-Mister-YT 
Free Download / Stream: https://bit.ly/s-t-mr-slowly
Music promoted by Audio Library https://youtu.be/b4p9TiftgJY

MARCAS TEMPORAIS:
0:00 - O que é o Portuguese with Leo? (em inglês)
1:08 - O que é o Portuguese with Leo? (em português)
4:29 - Método tradicional vs. Método natural
7:27 - Os objetivos deste canal

sentences: Learn European Portuguese with Portuguese With Leo [EN, PT subtitles]
Good morning everyone and welcome to Portuguese With Leo!
Before we get into the video I'd just like to start off by saying a few words in English,
just to quickly explain who this Youtube channel is for and how you can make the most of it.
My name is Leonardo and I created this Youtube channel for anyone who's interested in improving
your Portuguese, specifically European Portuguese, which is the variety we speak here in
Portugal, where I am from.
Although this channel is mainly for intermediate-level Portuguese students, it can also be useful for you.
from it even if you're a beginner, because I'll be speaking slowly, clearly and using
easy and simple words.
Even if you feel that the video's a little hard to follow at first, you can always slow
slow down the playback speed and I promise that over time it will become easier
to understand Portuguese.
You can also turn on the subtitles in this video or go to my website portuguesewithleo.com
to find the transcript of each video.
All the videos are also available in podcast format on all major platforms.
That said, let's start speaking Portuguese!
Now that I've done the presentation in English, the rest of this video and the other videos
on this channel are going to be exclusively in Portuguese.
As I said before, this channel is for people who are learning Portuguese and can't
find anything interesting on the internet to listen to.
There are 3 main levels of students of Portuguese: beginners are those
who are beginning to learn the language and need to study the most basic things.
They need to learn to say "hello", "good morning", "thank you", and for them there are many resources,
many materials to learn the basics of the language.
Advanced students, on the other hand, already have a great command of the language and are able to
read novels, watch movies, series or soap operas made for native Portuguese speakers.
For intermediate level students, however, there are almost no resources to
practice Portuguese, especially Portuguese from Portugal.
For Brazilian Portuguese there are many Youtube channels and other podcasts on the internet, but for
those who want to learn European Portuguese there is almost nothing out there.
What I want to do with this podcast (and Youtube channel) is help you improve your Portuguese,
specifically European Portuguese, by talking about various interesting topics,
or at least topics that I find interesting and that I hope you'll find too.
Obviously, I will talk a lot about Portugal, about Portuguese History and culture,
and about life in Portugal today, but I will also talk about other countries,
about current affairs, and about other topics such as philosophy, psychology and personal development.
I know that your main motivation to listen to this podcast is to improve your Portuguese,
so I'll also talk a great deal about language learning, which is a subject that fascinates me a lot.
topic that fascinates me a lot.
I have always had a great passion for languages and at the moment I speak 6 languages: Portuguese,
which is my mother tongue, and from the language I speak best to the language I speak the least
well, English, Spanish, Italian, French and German.
I don't say this to brag.
Oh, what is bragging?
To brag is to speak well or say well of something or something, and in this case to brag would be
say well about myself, as in English to brag.
I don't say this to brag, but to let you know that I already have experience.
to learn foreign languages and to be able to share with you all the tips and advice
that I have learned over the years so that your Portuguese learning can
be fast and effective.
This is exactly what I want to talk about in this episode: what are the best methods
to learn Portuguese and how you can use the Portuguese With Leo podcast from
best form.
First, it is necessary to distinguish between the traditional way of learning languages,
that which is present in most schools, and the natural method, that which is used by the
most polyglots and language lovers.
Ah, what is a polyglot?
A polyglot is a person who speaks several languages, usually 5 or more.
Starting with the traditional method, this is the one that is most present in most
of schools.
Surely you who are listening to me, if you went to school, will have learned at least
a foreign language.
In Portugal, for example, we learn English as the main foreign language and French
or Spanish as a second foreign language.
In these language classes, the typical thing is to study the language as you study other subjects.
Studying a lot of complicated grammar and learning vocabulary lists that are often not needed
This makes learning frustrating and boring, and we usually leave these classes with a lot of theory,
but when we try to speak the language in practice,
we can't speak naturally because we're very worried.
thinking about what the correct form of grammar will be or what the right word is that we can't remember.
remember.
